@peterjc Its a bit difficult for me to say for sure what should or should not currently work for recipes as I believe there have been several changes (since the original installation code was written) that may affect installations.  The original intent was to not use $INSTALL_DIR for the software download and compile steps, but rather to move compiled files to that directory as a final step of the installation recipe.  

The installation process automatically creates a temporary working directory in which the downloads are placed when using the download_by_url and download_file actions.  In the past this temporary working directory was not readily accessible within recipes, but I recently added support for using a new $TMP_WORK_DIR reserved word in ways similar to the use of $INSTALL_DIR.  This reserved word points to the temporary working directory root for us within the download and compile steps.  This allows for cleaner installations for more complex recipes that may install more than a single package (e.g., install Python and then install bumpy into that Python).  An example of a recipe that uses this approach is here:

https://github.com/gregvonkuster/galaxy-csg/blob/master/packages/package_icqsol_latest/tool_dependencies.xml

