@alexanderrichards Basically, if you just run a test such as:

```
class TestStartup(unittest.TestCase):
   def test_startup_submit(self):
      from ganga import *
      j = Job()
      j.submit()
      monitorUntilCompleted(j)   
```

Then everything will get unloaded/destroyed but e.g. your job may not get flushed to disk. If you add the decorator, this can add the call to anything that is added to atexit and properly flush, etc. It may be a separate function isn't needed and it can all be put in the decorator, but it may be nice just to have everything properly documented and separated: e.g. `atstartup()` and `atshutdown` functions in `ganga/__init__.py`

